No. This is SQL syntax, not WebQL. WebQL uses JSON structure:

{
  "@url": "https://example.com",
  "@steps": [
    {
      "@xpath": "//div[@class='product']",
      "@fields": {
        "name": ".//text()"
      }
    }
  ]
}

WebQL never uses SELECT, FROM, WHERE - it uses @url, @steps, @xpath, @fields.

No. This is GraphQL syntax, not WebQL. WebQL uses JSON structure:

{
  "@url": "https://example.com",
  "@steps": [
    {
      "@xpath": "//div[@class='product']",
      "@fields": {
        "name": ".//h3/text()",
        "price": ".//span[@class='price']/text()"
      }
    }
  ]
}

WebQL never uses 'query {' syntax - it uses JSON with @ keywords.

